### Get summary for user 1
### Expected: totalPayments=4, totalAmount=275,
### methodBreakdown={"CREDIT_CARD":195,"CASH":50,"WALLET":30}
GET http://localhost:8080/api/payments/user/1/summary

###

### Get summary for user with no payments
### Create a payment for user 2 first to ensure user 2 exists in users table
### then test a user that has no COMPLETED payments
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rideId": 6,
  "userId": 6,
  "amount": 40.0,
  "method": "CASH",
  "status": "PENDING",
  "createdAt": "2026-03-20T14:00:00"
}

###

### User with no COMPLETED payments - expect totalPayments=0, totalAmount=0
GET http://localhost:8080/api/payments/user/6/summary

###

### Non-existent user - expect 404
GET http://localhost:8080/api/payments/user/999/summary